Hi Kaisheng,

In win10, it will show the "WindowsError: [Error 126] The specified module could not be found" hints after processed "import uiautomation as automation";

I took my attention with KB971513 patch but that would not fit to win10. Specially, on the another win10 machine, that works well and didn't pop-up any error hint.

I guess there is something incompatible with UIAutomationClient.dll but have no idea to fix it;
If you are free please have a look at it.
Thanks.

In the interest of helping out and since I used django-star-ratings.  I would be interested in contributing to an angularized widget.  I use an angularized version for my project.  I'll be dumping some pieces here.  And I will possibly setup a pull request later this week with a formal integration if you fellows are ok with that.

I'm providing the pieces now in case you guys want to take the time to do it yourselves with some building blocks.

I have an app that does stuff with Candidates hence that terminology
```
#javascript that is needed because I use django templates (override the curly's to be squares)
var app = angular.module('rabidhire', ['ang-drag-drop']).config(function($interpolateProvider){
    $interpolateProvider.startSymbol('[[').endSymbol(']]');
});

//ng-repeat does not have star divs populated at post
//link phase on candidate div...Still learning angular..should work..but doesn't
//http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17643681/angularjs-linking-to-elements-in-a-directive-that-uses-ng-repeat
app.directive('rhstar', [ '$window', function ($window) {
  return {
    link: function (scope, ielement) {
                $window.starRatings.bindRating(ielement[0]);
            }
    }
}]);
```

Angular template for widget
```
{% load i18n %}
<style>
    #[[ Candidate.ratings.id ]] .star-ratings-rating-full, #[[ Candidate.ratings.id ]] .star-ratings-rating-empty {
        width: [[  Candidate.ratings.icon_width ]]px;
        height: [[  Candidate.ratings.icon_height ]]px;
    }

    #[[ Candidate.ratings.id ]] .star-ratings-rating-empty {
        background-position: -[[  Candidate.ratings.icon_width ]]px 0;
    }

    {% if user.is_authenticated %}
    #[[ Candidate.ratings.id ]] .star-ratings-rating-full:hover, #[[ Candidate.ratings.id ]] .star-ratings-rating-empty:hover {
        background-position: -[[  Candidate.ratings.icon_width + Candidate.ratings.icon_width ]]px 0;
    }
    {% endif %}
</style>
<div id="[[ Candidate.ratings.id ]] " class="star-ratings" data-max-rating="[[ Candidate.ratings.star_count ]]" data-avg-rating="[[ Candidate.ratings.rating.average ]]">
    {% block rating_stars %}
        <div class="star-ratings-rating-stars-container">
            <ul class="star-ratings-rating-background">
                    <li  ng-cloak ng-repeat="star in Candidate.ratings.stars">
                        {% if user.is_authenticated %}
                        <a rhstar href="{{ ratings_url }}[[ Candidate.ratings.rating.content_type_id ]]/[[ Candidate.ratings.rating.object_id_hex ]]/?return={{ request.path }}" data-score="[[ star ]]" class="star-ratings-rate-action">
                            <span class="star-ratings-rating-empty"></span>
                        </a>
                        {% else %}
                            <span class="star-ratings-rating-empty" title="{% trans 'Log in to rate' as title_login %}{{ title_login|escape }}"></span>
                        {% endif %}
                    </li>
            </ul>

            <ul class="star-ratings-rating-foreground" style="width: [[ Candidate.ratings.percentage|str2num|number:2 ]]%">
                    <li ng-cloak ng-repeat="star in Candidate.ratings.stars">
                    {% if user.is_authenticated %}
                    <a rhstar href="{{ ratings_url }}[[ Candidate.ratings.rating.content_type_id ]]/[[ Candidate.ratings.rating.object_id_hex ]]/?return={{ request.path }}" data-score="[[ star ]]" class="star-ratings-rate-action">
                        <span class="star-ratings-rating-full"></span>
                    </a>
                    {% else %}
                        <span class="star-ratings-rating-full" title="Log in to rate"></span>
                    {% endif %}
                    </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    {% endblock %}
    {% block rating_detail %}
    {% block rating_average %}
    <div class="star-ratings-rating-average">{% trans 'Average: ' %} <span class='star-ratings-rating-value'>[[ Candidate.ratings.rating.average|str2num|number:2 ]]</span></div>
    {% endblock rating_average %}
    {% block rating_count %}
    <div class="star-ratings-rating-count">{% trans 'Rating Count: ' %} <span class='star-ratings-rating-value'>[[ Candidate.ratings.rating.count ]]</span></div>
    {% endblock rating_count %}
    {% block rating_user %}
    <div class="star-ratings-rating-user">{% trans 'You Rated: ' %} <span class='star-ratings-rating-value'>[[ Candidate.ratings.user_rating ? Candidate.ratings.user_rating.score : {% trans 'Not rated' %} ]]</span></div>
    {% if not user.is_authenticated %}
        <p>{% trans 'Please log in to rate.' %}</p>
    {% endif %}
    {% endblock rating_user %}
    <div class="star-ratings-errors"></div>
    {% endblock rating_detail %}
</div>
```

