Hi!

This might be a user error, but I think this looks like a bug to me.

MWE:

```
namespace ns {
    struct Pet {
        enum class Enum { val1, val2 };
    };
}

namespace f {
    void func(ns::Pet::Enum en) { return; }
}

PYBIND11_MODULE(mod, m) {
    py::class_<ns::Pet> pet(m, "Pet");

    pet.def(py::init<ns::Pet>());

    py::enum_<ns::Pet::Enum>(pet, "Enum")
        .value("Dog", ns::Pet::Enum::val1)
        .value("Cat", ns::Pet::Enum::val2)
        .export_values(); // with and without this line - it's the same result

    m.def("func", &f::func);
}
```

The enum is correctly usable as `mod.Pet.Enum`, however, the documentation for `func` is wrong (`help(mod.func)`):

> FUNCTIONS
    func(...) method of builtins.PyCapsule instance
        func(arg0: mod.Enum) -> None

where this should show mod.Pet.Enum.

